        {
          "ruleId": "CWE-78_armis-appsec-sample_38295677_completions/armis-cli.ps1_92_5_92_69",
          "ruleIndex": 3,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Injection (CWE-78: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an OS Command ('OS Command Injection')): The function builds `$RequestComp` from the command line the user is typing (`$Program` and `$Arguments`). This string is then passed directly to `Invoke-Expression`, which evaluates it as PowerShell code. No sanitization or escaping is applied before the call, so any characters supplied by the user can alter the command that is executed. An attacker controlling the command line can therefore inject and run arbitrary PowerShell commands, matching CWE‑78 (OS command injection). The code runs as part of a PowerShell argument completer, which is invoked whenever a user interacts with the shell, giving it immediate external exposure. Consequently, the vulnerability is a true positive."
          },
